The paper deals with the problem of online clustering, which is a topic in both data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.AI). The problem involves partitioning a graph into clusters, which is a topic in graph theory (cs.GT). The objective function being optimized is related to the number of edges in the clusters, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper proposes a strategy with a competitive ratio, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
